ReadMe

Drill ID: 2026_JD_06_W1_CampusDeviceAudit

Class Name: CampusDeviceAduit

Difficulty: Level 3 - Object-Oriented Problem Solving

Estimated Time: 70-90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 64 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Build a campus device inspection system using inheritance. Different device types share common fields and methods,
but each child class has its own inspection rules and state updates.

Requirements
- Create a parent class named CampusDevice.
- Create Projector and LabComputer child classes using extends.
- Override needsInspection() and inspect() in each child class.
- Store mixed device objects in an CampusDevice[] array.
- Use loops, conditions, and String comparison to print reports, inspect devices, and search by asset tag.

Learning Objective
Practice designing and inheritance hierarchy, separating parent and child responsibilites, overriding inherited methods,
and processing different object types through one parent type.